    <title>Three distinct types of hotspots in the Earth’s mantle</title>
    <url>/2024/08/01/Three%20distinct%20types%20of%20hotspots%20in%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20mantle/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h1>&gt; Abstract</h1>
<p>[[Courtillot_2003_EPSL.pdf#page=1&amp;selection=28,0,28,8|Courtillot_2003_EPSL, page 1]]</p>
<h2 id="Background">Background</h2>
<ul class="lvl-0">
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>The origin of mantle hotspots</p>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>only seven (‘primary’) out of 49 hotspots --&gt; a very deep origin</p>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>in each hemisphere these move slowly</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Scientific-Question-s-or-Phenomena">Scientific Question(s) or Phenomena</h2>
<ul class="lvl-0">
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>there has been up to 50 mm/a motion between the two hemispheres prior to 50 Ma ago</p>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>This correlates with latitudinal shifts in the Hawaiian and Reunion hotspots</p>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>with a change in true polar wander</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Methods">Methods</h2>
<h2 id="Conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
<ul class="lvl-0">
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>hotspots may come from distinct mantle boundary layer</p>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p><mark>the primary ones trace shifts in quadrupolar convection in the lower mantle</mark></p>
<ul class="lvl-2">
<li class="lvl-6">trace
<ul class="lvl-4">
<li class="lvl-10">make a mark or lines on a surface</li>
<li class="lvl-10">ascertain  the course of development of something</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="lvl-6">quadrupolar convection?</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h1>&gt; Introduction</h1>
<p>[[Courtillot_2003_EPSL.pdf#page=1&amp;selection=42,4,42,15|Courtillot_2003_EPSL, page 1]]</p>
<ul class="lvl-0">
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>Origin of volcanoes remote from plate boundaries</p>
<ul class="lvl-2">
<li class="lvl-6">Deep mantle plumes created in the lowermost mantle</li>
<li class="lvl-6">Tensional cracking of the lithosphere</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="lvl-3">
<p>Five criteria to sort the hotspot catalogues</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h1>&gt; Five possible characteristics of a deep plume</h1>
<p>[[Courtillot_2003_EPSL.pdf#page=2&amp;selection=16,4,16,48|Courtillot_2003_EPSL, page 2]]</p>
<ul class="lvl-0">
<li class="lvl-2">
<p><mark>Temperature-dependent viscosity fluid --&gt; mushroom-shaped head and a thin, long stem --&gt;</mark></p>
<ul class="lvl-2">
<li class="lvl-6">(1) long-lived tracks</li>
<li class="lvl-6">(2) <mark>traps at their initiation</mark></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="lvl-2">
<p>Plumes coming from the bottom of the mantle with a buoyancy flux of less than <mjx-container class="MathJax" jax="SVG"><svg style="vertical-align: -0.464ex;" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="10.436ex" height="2.417ex" role="img" focusable="false" viewBox="0 -863.3 4612.7 1068.3"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="scale(1,-1)"><g data-mml-node="math"><g data-mml-node="msup"><g data-mml-node="mn"><path data-c="31" d="M213 578L200 573Q186 568 160 563T102 556H83V602H102Q149 604 189 617T245 641T273 663Q275 666 285 666Q294 666 302 660V361L303 61Q310 54 315 52T339 48T401 46H427V0H416Q395 3 257 3Q121 3 100 0H88V46H114Q136 46 152 46T177 47T193 50T201 52T207 57T213 61V578Z"></path><path data-c="30" d="M96 585Q152 666 249 666Q297 666 345 640T423 548Q460 465 460 320Q460 165 417 83Q397 41 362 16T301 -15T250 -22Q224 -22 198 -16T137 16T82 83Q39 165 39 320Q39 494 96 585ZM321 597Q291 629 250 629Q208 629 178 597Q153 571 145 525T137 333Q137 175 145 125T181 46Q209 16 250 16Q290 16 318 46Q347 76 354 130T362 333Q362 478 354 524T321 597Z" transform="translate(500,0)"></path></g><g data-mml-node="mn" transform="translate(1033,393.1) scale(0.707)"><path data-c="33" d="M127 463Q100 463 85 480T69 524Q69 579 117 622T233 665Q268 665 277 664Q351 652 390 611T430 522Q430 470 396 421T302 350L299 348Q299 347 308 345T337 336T375 315Q457 262 457 175Q457 96 395 37T238 -22Q158 -22 100 21T42 130Q42 158 60 175T105 193Q133 193 151 175T169 130Q169 119 166 110T159 94T148 82T136 74T126 70T118 67L114 66Q165 21 238 21Q293 21 321 74Q338 107 338 175V195Q338 290 274 322Q259 328 213 329L171 330L168 332Q166 335 166 348Q166 366 174 366Q202 366 232 371Q266 376 294 413T322 525V533Q322 590 287 612Q265 626 240 626Q208 626 181 615T143 592T132 580H135Q138 579 143 578T153 573T165 566T175 555T183 540T186 520Q186 498 172 481T127 463Z"></path></g></g><g data-mml-node="mi" transform="translate(1436.6,0)"><path data-c="1D458" d="M121 647Q121 657 125 670T137 683Q138 683 209 688T28